   {:e #blake3 "0c1e3ca79533ef2f44adce864c0cb48def4c51eba7a06ad6c05bff2225bde17e" :a :harvest/accomplishments :v "Session entity: :task/t-8bdd3e96; CE-OAR FORMULA FIX: The dampening formula in CE-OAR step (4) is INVERTED. dampening_factor = 0.3 * (1.0 - max_overlap) produces LESS dampening when overlap is HIGH (opposite of intent). CORRECT formula: dampening_factor = max(0.1, 1.0 - 0.7 * max_overlap). At max_overlap=1.0: factor=0.3 (heavy dampening). At max_overlap=0.0: factor=1.0 (no dampening). At max_overlap=0.5: factor=0.65 (moderate). This ensures explored tasks sink while unexplored tasks maintain their base impact.; CE-TEST MISSING COVERAGE: 4 task areas have zero test coverage in CE-TEST (t-be245b63). MISSING-1 CE-COGNITION (8 acceptance criteria): cognitive_tick with new observations, FileExists check, ImportCheck for Go/Rust/Python, TestCoverage counting test files, daemon findings as observations in store, findings in braid status output, tick completes in <500ms, no regression. MISSING-2 CE-META (5 criteria): PhrasingPattern enum tracking per hypothesis, pattern weight calibration from outcomes, cross-project CRDT merge of pattern weights, uniform bootstrap weights on empty store, C8 substrate-independent patterns. MISSING-3 CE-STEER (6 criteria): compile_hypothesis_prompt at T=0.1 contains file path, at T=0.9 is broad, shared keywords at medium T, hole-type determines phrasing structure (beta0/beta1/beta2 -> bridge/falsification/void), PhrasingPattern tag on every hypothesis, no raw EntityId hex in output. MISSING-4 CE-TOPO (7 criteria): 3 disconnected clusters -> beta0=3, circular path detected -> beta1>=1, boundary observation proxy -> beta2>0, topology line in braid status, falsification hypothesis for H1, void-exploration hypothesis for H2, Euler characteristic. TOTAL: 26 acceptance criteria with zero test coverage. CE-TEST must be updated to include test scenarios 16-30 covering these.; Meta-Learning Pattern Transfer; Session entity: :recon/trace-e91d3cb261683776; Session entity: :recon/trace-78395c2277ae69e2; Session entity: :recon/trace-dc6999f83ce62a95; Session entity: :recon/trace-c23a644994a3c051; FIVE LOOP CLOSURES VERIFICATION CHECKLIST: The 4.0/10 dogfood score traces to 5 unclosed loops. Each must be verified independently. LOOP-1 OAR: After N observations in area X, tasks about X DROP in R(t) ranking. VERIFY: run braid observe 3x about consistency, then braid task ready — consistency task must not be top-3. LOOP-2 SEED: braid seed on external project shows project knowledge, not braid self-description. VERIFY: braid seed on Go CLI — orientation section mentions Go packages, not 'append-only datom store'. LOOP-3 BOUNDARY: braid status shows boundary metric after alignment observations. VERIFY: after 3 'aligned' and 1 'divergent' observations, boundaries line shows '3/4 75%'. LOOP-4 LABELS: bridge hypotheses contain observation text and file paths, not session IDs. VERIFY: FEGH output contains no ':session/s-' prefixes. LOOP-5 M(t): M(t) changes during session as agent works. VERIFY: M(t) before observations != M(t) after 5 observations. ALL FIVE must pass for convergence engine to be validated.; Session entity: :recon/trace-ed9f0f2355bba21c; THEORETICAL-CONVERGENCE: Nine mathematical frameworks converge on the SAME optimality condition for hypothesis generation. (1) Information theory: maximize mutual information I(H;O). (2) Active inference/Friston: minimize expected free energy G(h). (3) Bayesian optimization: UCB alpha=mu+beta*sigma where beta=temperature. (4) Differential geometry: follow the natural gradient I^{-1} * nabla-F. (5) Algebraic topology: target boundary of topological hole (H0/H1/H2). (6) Quantum mechanics: choose measurement basis maximizing information about quantity of interest. (7) Category theory: hypothesis is the unit of the observation-projection adjunction. (8) Socratic method: connect two known-but-unlinked concepts in zone of proximal development. (9) Control theory: optim